<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880428-0090 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief: WPP Group PLC </HL><SO> </SO><CO> WPPGY </CO><IN> TNM </IN><TEXT>   WPP Group PLC said it agreed to acquire EWA Ltd., a British marketing services company, for as much as #22.1 million ($41.3 million).    WPP, a London-based advertising and marketing services company, said it will make an initial payment of #4.8 million in cash and stock, followed by annual payments through 1993 in amounts that will depend on EWA's profitability. EWA applies data-base management techniques to help clients locate potential customers who they can reach through direct marketing.    WPP, which said it is trying to broaden the range of its services, estimated that the U.S. market for direct marketing services totals $19 billion, that the British market is nearly $2 billion and that the market will grow 15% to 20% a year world-wide. </TEXT></DOC>